Chiles Rellenos Recipe:

7-8 poblano peppers
2 lbs @donfranciscocheese oaxaca cheese
5 egg whites
3 egg yolks
1//4 tsp salt
1/8 tsp cream of tartar
1 tbsp all purpose flour
Extra all purpose flour for dusting chiles
Vegetable oil 

Instructions: 
Roast chiles poblanos for 2 minutes on each side on open fire. Add them to a bag so they steam for 7-10 minutes. Carefully peel them and cut a small slit on the side of your chile and remove seeds and veins on the inside (making sure chile doesn't completely open).
Stuff your chiles with as much cheese as you can then add seal them with toothpicks if needed (don't forget to remove them before eating them). Now, dust the stuffed chiles with flour.
Separate your eggs and reserve 5 egg whites and 3 egg yolks. Fluff up your egg whites with a hand mixer. Once they've fluffed up, add cream of tartar and salt and mix again until egg whites are super stiff. Add 3 egg yolks and mix in very quick. Lastly, add in your 1 tbsp of flour and fold it in with a spatula so your eggs don't deflate. Dip your chiles and fry on each side. Then add them to the sauce and serve with red rice on the side.

Red Sauce:
10 roma tomatoes
1/2 onion
5 garlic cloves
Chicken bouillon to taste
3 cups water
3 tbsps oil

Instructions:
Roast everything, then add everything back to blender with chicken bouillon and water, then blend and fry with 3 tbsps of oil. Cook until thickened to your liking.

Follow to be part of my type 1 diabetes journey and for more delicious recipes🔥

Birria Ramen Recipe:

Meat:
4 lbs chuck roast
1/2 onion
4 garlic cloves
2 bayleaves
7 guajillo peppers
3 pasilla ancho peppers
6 chiles de arbol

1 roasted tomato
1/4 tsp cumin
1/4 tsp peppercorns
2 whole cloves
1/2 stick cinnamon
1 tbsp chicken bouillon
Salt to taste
2 cups water you cooked chiles in

Instructions:
Cover your meat with water, add onion garlic and bayleaves. Once meat reaches a boil; clean your broth and add your dried chiles to your pot. 
Now blend together your softened peppers, onion, garlic cloves and bay leaves that you previously boiled, roasted tomato, spices, 1 tbsp chicken bouillon + salt to taste with 2 cups of water you cooked chiles in. Strain the sauce you blended and add it to your pot after that first boil and then cover on medium high heat for 2 hours or until your meat is fork tender.

Now boil your ramen noodles (follow instructions in the back of your noodle packet). My noodles cook in 4 minutes! Add noodles to a bowl, add lots of broth, some shredded birria meat and top with cilantro, onion and spicy salsa!

#diabeticsuperkid #type1diabetes #kidswithdiabetes #kidsthatcook #mexicanfood #birria #birriaramen #explorepage #ramen #comidamexicana

Refried Pork Beans Recipe:

Ingredients:
1 cup mayocaba beans
2 garlic cloves
1 jalapeño
2.5 liters water
1 package of @caciquefoods chorizo
1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
Salt (to taste)

Instructions:

To a 5 quart dutch over add your beans, garlic, jalapeño, water and fork, Put the heat on high, once they reach a boil, cook your beans until tender (about 90 minutes).

Add a little bit of avocado oil to a very hot cast iron and fry your chorizo until cooked half way, then add your beans and fry them with chorizo until theirs no more grease. Now add 1 cup of bean juice and cook until  very soft. Once they're soft, mash them and add 1 or 2 more cup of bean juice (add more or less bean juice depending on how soft you like your beans). When beans reach a boil, add 1 cup of mozzarella shredded cheese. Let them reach a boil and they're ready to add to a flour tortilla!!

NOTE: if at any moment you feel that your beans need more water, make sure that you boil the water before adding it to your beans, NEVER add cold water!

#diabeticsuperkid #refriedbeans #frijoles #mexicanfood #comidamexicana #burritos #beanburritos #kidsthatcook #explorepage

Carne En Su Jugo Recipe:
1 lb bacon (chopped in big squares)
3 bunches of green onion 
2 jalapeño peppers

Instructions:

Today I put the biggest smile on Momma when I showed her the delicious frijoles de la olla, salsa molcajetada & corn tortillas I made for her❤️

#AD She was even more surprised when she saw I washed the dishes! Thank you to @alenproductsusa for partnering up with me today! The dish soap did not only make it easier to wash the dishes, BUT it made it even better because it smelled like my favorite candy "APPLE JOLLY RANCHERS"😍
In case you're wondering, I found all these products at @elsupermarkets !

-----------------------------
Frijoles De La Olla Recipe:

Ingredients:
1 1/2 cups mayocaba beans
1 serrano pepper
4 garlic cloves
12 cups water

Instructions:
Add everything to a 5 quart pot and once everything reaches a boil cook on medium heat for 90 minutes or until beans are tender.

------------------------

Salsa Molcajeteada:

Ingredients:
2 roma tomatoes
2 small tomatillos
1 jalapeño 
2 serranos
1/4 onion
2 garlic cloves
Salt (to taste)

Instructions:
Char all your ingredients! Once charred, remove them from the comal. With your molcajete grind onion, garlic and salt together until you form a paste, then add peppers and grind (leave it chunky but make sure the pieces aren't too big). Now add tomatoes and tomatillos and mash them really well! 

Serve your frijoles de la olla, top with your salsa molcajeteada and queso fresco!

-------------------------

Tortillas de Maiz:

2 1/2 cups yellow maseca
1 tsp salt
1 cup water (more or less as needed)

Instructions:
Add your water and salt to your corn masa flour and mix it until your masa dough is very smooth and pliable like clay (it takes about 10 minutes of kneading by hand). Let your masa rest for 20 minutes then roll your masa into equal balls (testales) and flatten them with tortilla press. 

Add your tortilla to a very hot comal and as soon as the edges lift up, flip your tortilla. Then, as soon as your tortilla starts to lightly bubble up flip again and tap in the middle. Once your tortilla blows up into a big bubble, you know it cooked through❣️

Arroz Con Leche Recipe

Ingredients:

2 cups extra long grain rice
2 cinnamon sticks
Lemon peel (3 medium pieces)
3 cups water

1/2 gallon milk
2 cans of evaporated milks
1 can of lechera
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/8 tsp salt

Ground Cinnamon (Optional)
Chopped Walnuts (Optional)
Raisins (Optional)

Instructions:

Give your rice a quick rinse to clean it but don't overdo it because we need the starch! Add your clean rice to a pot; add cinnamon sticks, lemon peel and 3 cups of water. Once it reaches a boil cover on low for 15 minutes or until rice has fully cooked. Add milk, evaporated milk, lechera, vanilla extract and salt to a pot until hot (don't let it boil). Add milk back to the cooked rice and constantly mix on medium low heat until it reaches your desire consistency. (don't forget to remove cinnamon stick and lemon peel). Top and enjoy with ground cinnamon and walnuts! You can add raisins too but I'm not a big fan of them!

-------------------------------

ESPAÑOL

Receta De Arroz Con Leche

Ingredientes:

2 tazas de arroz de grano extralargo
2 ramas de canela
Cáscara de limón amarillo (3 trozos medianos)
3 tazas de agua

1/2 galón de leche
2 latas de leches evaporadas
1 lata de lechera
1 cucharada de extracto de vainilla
1/8 cucharadita de sal

Canela molida (opcional)
Nueces picadas (opcional)
Pasas (opcional)

Instrucciones:

Enjuaga rápidamente tu arroz para limpiarlo, ¡pero no te excedas porque necesitamos el almidón! Agrega tu arroz limpio a una olla; agrega las ramas de canela, la cáscara de limón y 3 tazas de agua. Una vez que hierva, cubra a fuego lento durante 15 minutos o hasta que el arroz esté completamente cocido. Agrega a una olla la leche, la leche evaporada, la lechera, el extracto de vainilla y la sal hasta que esté caliente (no dejes que hierva). Vuelva a agregar la leche al arroz cocido y mezcle constantemente a fuego medio bajo hasta que alcance la consistencia deseada (no olvides remover las canelas y la cascara de limon). ¡Cubra y disfrute con canela molida y nueces! ¡También puedes agregar pasas, pero no soy fan de ellas!

Albondigas Recipe:

(I bought all of my ingredients including the clay bowls and plates at @vallarta.supermarkets 🙃)

Meatballs:
1.5 lbs ground beef
1 lbs ground pork
1/2 finely chopped onion
3 minced garlic cloves
3 sprigs of hierba buena/mint finely chopped
1 grated italian zucchini 
1 egg
1/4 cup white rice
1/4 tsp dried oregano
Salt and pepper to taste

Instructions:
Mix all of your meatball ingredients together then form your meatballs.

Caldo/Broth:
7 large roma tomatoes
1/4 onion
3 garlic cloves
1/4 tsp oregano
2-3 chipotle peppers
3/4 cup water

2 liters water

Instructions:
Blend all of your broth ingredients and add to a hot pot and fry until slightly thickened then add chicken bouillon to taste and 2 liters of water then bring to a boil and add meatballs for 25 minutes.

Vegetables:
2 carrots
5 red potatoes 
1 italian zucchini 
1 chayote (optional)

Instructions:
Once meatballs cook for 25 minutes on medium heat; add carrots, 5 minutes later add potatoes and chayote and 18 minutes later add zuchinni and 5 minutes later YOU'RE done!

-----------------------------

RED RICE RECIPE:

Red Sauce Ingredients:
4 small ripe roma tomatoes
1/4 onion
2-3 garlic cloves

3 tbsps avocado oil
2 smashed garlic cloves 
2 cups extra long white rice

Add your avocado oil and fry your garlic cloves until aromatic, then add your rice and fry until golden brown. Now blend your red sauce ingredients then add it to your rice and fry it until it has reduced and lightly fried, now add..

3 cups of water
Knorr chicken bouillon to taste
1 serrano pepper

Once everything reaches a boil cover on low for 20 minutes. Then once the 20 minutes are up, turn off the heat and LEAVE THE PAN CLOSED for an an addition 20 minutes. Fluff up your rice and it's ready to serve.

2 lbs beef stew meat

Instructions: Boil 3 liters of water with Meat, bones, salt and FORK. Cook on high heat and let it reach a boil then skim off all the impurities. Now add 1/2 onion, 4 garlic cloves & 2 bayleaves. Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.

Chef Merito steak seasoning to taste

1/4 onion
4 garlic cloves

This song makes my Momma cry every single time because it reminds her a lot of Grandpa Pat😭 So today I'm dedicating this video to my Grandpa Pat because he loved Momma's cooking so much, especially her Pozole Blanco🤍

Pork:
2 pigs feet split in half
3 lbs boneless pork cushion (cubed)
4 pieces of pork neckbkne
1/2 onion
5 garlic cloves
2 bayleaves
3 liters water

Instructions:
Add pig feet, pork cushion and pork neckbone to an 8 quart pot and cover with 3 liters of water, cook on high heat. Let pozole blanco cook for 20-30 minutes on medium heat. Now serve and top with shredded cabbage, onion, red raddishes and enjoy!

Atole de Galletas Maria con Nuez

7 cups whole milk
1 tbsp mexican vanilla
1 cinnamon stick
1 can carnation evaporated milk
150 grams galletas maria (1 pack)
1 cup walnuts
2-3 mini piloncillos (to taste)

Instructions:

To a 4 quart pot add 4 cups of milk, 1 cinnamon stick plus 2 tbsps of mexican vanilla. Cover and cook on medium heat.

Now blend 3 cups of whole milk, 1 can of evaporated milk, 1 pack of galletas maria + 1 cup of walnuts. 

Once milk reaches a boil, add your cookie nut milk mixture + 2 to 3 mini piloncillos. Cook on low heat until your piloncillo is melted and enjoy with pan dulce from Vallarta Supermarkets!!

Arrachera-Chorizo Huarache (Low Carb Version)

Frijoles de la olla:

2 cups mayocaba beans
11 cups water 
3 garlic cloves
1/4 onion
1 jalapeño
1 tbsp salt

4 tbsps avocado oil
3 thick strands of Oaxaca cheese

Instructions:
Add your beans, water, garlic cloves, 1/4 onion and jalapeño to a 4 quart pot! Cook on high and once it reaches a boil cook on low for 80 minutes. Once your beans are fully cooked, add the salt and cook on low for 10 more minutes then add everything back to the blender and blend everything together + 2 cups of water and 1 tsp of salt.

Now add 4 tbsps of avocado oil to your pan and fry your beans. Once they reach a boil add a couple strands of Oaxaca cheese and once the cheese has melted, they're ready to enjoy!

-------------------------------

Green Salsa:

3 garlic cloves 
1/4 onion
2 jalapeños
4 serranos
8 really small tomatillos

1/2 bunch of cilantro
1 tbsp chicken bouillon

Instructions:
To a small pot; add garlic cloves, onion, jalapeños and serranos. Cover with water and cook them on medium heat just until peppers change in color (10-12 mins).

At this point add tomatillos and cook them just until they change in color as well (this will only take about 5 mins) Don't overcook them because if they burst, your salsa will come out bitter! 

Once everything is done cooking; blend it with cilantro and chicken bouillon , Y LISTO!

------------------------------------

Huarache:

Nopalitos

Instructions: Fry nopal for 2-3 minutes on each side on high heat just until the nopales change in color! Then top with cheese, 1/4 scoop beans, arrachera, chorizo, mexican crema, queso cotija, cilantro, avocado and green salsa!

A lot of the questions that I get as a type 1 diabetic are “what can you eat?” “how many carbs can you eat?” “does it hurt to poke yourself?” but I feel like I don’t get asked enough... “How would you treat an emergency low blood sugar if you were to be extremely low or unconscious?” My answer is Gvoke HypoPen® (glucagon injection). The steps are simple; Pull the red cap off, push and hold the yellow end down against your skin at one of the approved injections sites and slowly count to 5. Call for emergency medical help after Gvoke HypoPen® has been injected.

Patients can even administer Gvoke HypoPen® to themselves in certain situations! For full detailed instructions on how or when to use Gvoke HypoPen® go to www.gvokeglucagon.com Click my link in bio to learn more about it. #GvokeHypoPen #Gvoke #HypoHappens

What is GVOKE? GVOKE is a prescription medicine used to treat very low blood sugar (severe hypoglycemia) in people with diabetes ages 2 years and above. It is not known if GVOKE is safe and effective in children under 2 years of age. 

Do not use GVOKE if: you have a tumor in the gland on top of your kidneys (adrenal gland) called a pheochromocytoma, as it may cause a substantial increase in blood pressure; you have a tumor in your pancreas called an insulinoma, as it may cause low blood sugar; or if you are allergic to glucagon or any inactive ingredient in GVOKE. 

GVOKE may cause other serious side effects, such as Serious skin rash — in certain people with a tumor in their pancreas called a glucagonoma; Serious allergic reactions — Call your doctor or get medical help right away if you have a serious allergic reaction including rash, difficulty breathing, low blood pressure. 

See Important Safety Information and Full Prescribing Information in our profile highlights.

US-SM-GVK-23-00069

4-6 chiles de arbol

1 roasted tomato
1/4 tsp cumin

Instructions:
Cover your meat with water, add onion garlic and bayleaves. Once meat reaches a boil; clean your broth and add your dried chiles to your pot.

Now boil your ramen noodles (follow instructions in the back of your noodle packet). My noodles cook in 4 minutes! Add noodles to a bowl, add lots of broth, some shredded birria meat and top with cilantro, onion and spicy salsa!

Champurrado Recipe:

Everytime we make champurrado it usually sticks to the bottom of my pots, so THANK YOU @bydash for sending me Iron Chef @geoffreyzakarian Trupro 10 piece nonstick stainless steel cookware set❤️ So far every single pan and pot has been amazing!!

1 liter water
1 big cinnamon stick
2 chocolate abuelita tablets
1 liter milk

1.5 cups water
200 grams masa para tortillas from @vallartasupermarkets
1/2 can of lechera (add all of it if you like it sweeter)

Instructions:
In a 5 quart zakarian trupro sauce pan; add 1 liter of water and 1 big cinnamon stick. Once it reaches a boil add 2 tablets of chocolate abuelita until dissolved. Once it reaches a boil again, add your milk and let it heat on medium heat.

To a blender, add 1.5 cups of water, 200 grams of masa and 1/2 a can of lechera (sweetness is to taste, so you can add more or less).

Once everything is perfectly blended; add it back to your chocolate mixture. Mix continuously on medium heat until you reach desired thickness!

Frijoles Puercos Recipe:

Thank you @vallarta.supermarkets for my super awesome Christmas Sweater!!🎄Also, I got all these delish ingredients at Vallarta Supermarkets as well🔥

Ingredients:
2 cups mayocaba beans
3 garlic cloves
1 jalapeño
3 liters water
1/4 cup sliced pickled jalapeños
1/4 cup pickled jalapeño juice
1/3 lb  of @vallarta.supermarkets chorizo
12 oz bacon
4 turkey franks 
4 strands of oaxaca cheese
Salt (to taste)

Instructions:

To a pot add your beans, garlic, jalapeño, water and fork, Put the heat on high, once they reach a boil, cook your beans until tender (about 90 minutes).

Chop you bacon and turkey franks. Fry bacon first then remove from pan and fry turkey franks in bacon oil. Now in a very hot cast iron fry chorizo then add your beans back and fry until all chorizo oil has been absorbed. Add 1 cup of bean juice + jalapeños and jalapeño juice. Cook until  very soft. Once they're soft, mash them and add 1 or 2 more cup of bean juice (add more or less bean juice depending on how soft you like your beans). When beans reach a boil, add oaxaca cheese. Let them reach a boil and they're ready to add to a flour tortilla!!

NOTE: if at any moment you feel that your beans need more water, make sure that you boil the water before adding it to your beans, NEVER add cold water!

Holiday Chicken Crescent Wreath (Corona de Pollo) Recipe:

Ingredients:

1 big shredded chicken breast
1 diced small green apple
1 diced red bell pepper
1 minced garlic clove
1/4 minced onion
1 chopped walnuts
1 cup cranberries
1.5 cups mayonnaise 
1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
1-2 tbsps diced chipotles in adobo
1/2 tsp crushed black pepper
1 tsp chicken bouillon
Salt to taste

Toppings:

Egg wash
Sesame seeds
Reserved tiny dough balls

2 (12 oz) Pillsbury Butter Flake Crescents
1 egg white (to brush wreath)
Sesame seads (sprinkle on top of wreath)

Instructions:
To an 8 qt pot; add chicken breast, onion, garlic and bay leaves. Add a fork and cover with water. Cook on high heat and once it reaches a boil lower to mesium heat. Cook for a total of 40 minutes then remove from pot and shred with a hand mixer.

Now add the rest of your ingredients to the chicken and mix until it comes together.

Open 2 pillsbury crescent roll cans and spread them in a shape of a sun. Roll the dough a little thinner, so your corona doesn't come out doughy (remove any excess and use it to make little decorations balls for the top of the corona).
With an ice cream scooper add filling to the corona, seal and brush with egg wash and top with your tiny dough balls and sesame seeds.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees and bake your corona de pollo for 30 minutes or until golden brown! Enjoy and Happy Holidays!!

Low Sugar Bread Pudding with Vanilla Cream

39 carbs per serving 
(This entire pan has 12 servings)

Ingredients
Bread Pudding:
3 cups whole milk
1 ½ cups monk fruit
¼ cup butter, melted
3 eggs
½ teaspoon ground cinnamon
11 slices texas toast
3/4 cup craisins
3/4 cup chopped walnuts

Vanilla Sauce:
1 ¼ cups whole milk
½ cup monk fruit
2 tablespoons butter, melted
1 egg
1 tablespoon all-purpose flour
1/8 tsp ground cinnamon
1/8 tsp salt
1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract

Instructions:

Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. Grease a 1/4 of sheet rectangular pan. 

For the bread pudding part; start by mixing eggs, monk fruit and cinnamon. Once it's incorporated; mix in the melted butter and add the milk little by little while you whisk, so your mixture doesn't separate. Add the liquid to your toasted bread cubes, walnuts and craisins. Now add mixture into the greased pan. Bake for 20 minutes then cover with aluminum foil and cook for 30 more minutes. Remove from the oven and pour vanilla cream sauce over and top with craisins and walnuts!

For vanilla sauce part, whisk together melted butter, egg, milk, monkfruit , flour, cinnamon, and salt in a saucepan until smooth. Cook over medium high heat (whisking constantly until sauce thickens up).

Mexican Mac Salad Recipe:

16 oz short pasta
12 oz frozen peas and veggie mix
1 can corn (drained)
1/2 pound deli sliced ham (diced)
6 hard boiled eggs (diced)
3 tbsps jalapeño pickled juice
2.5 cups mayonnaise 
1 tbsp dijon mustard
2 tsps black pepper
Salt to taste

Instructions:

In a 8 qt pot, boil 4 quarts of water. Once it reaches a boil add pasta and cook for 11 minutes. Drain pasta and rinse with cold water to stop cooking. In a small pot cook frozen veggies for 2 minutes then strain and to the pasta, then rinse again to stop the cooking as well. 

Once pasta and veggies have cooled down; add corn, eggs, ham, jalapeño pickled juice, salt, pepper and dijon mustard! Mix and let it chill in the fridge for a couple hours before you enjoy with a saladita and some jalapeños!

Frijoles Charros Recipe

You can buy all of these ingredients at @vallarta.supermarkets 🔥

Frijoles De La Olla:

3 cups mayocaba beans
1 serrano pepper
4 garlic cloves
3.5 liters water

Charros Ingredients:

10 slices bacon (chopped)
4 weenies (chopped)
1/2 lb pork chorizo 
2 roma tomatoes (diced)
1/4 onion (diced)
2 garlic cloves (minced)
2 cups chicharron
Small handful of cilantro (roughly chopped)
Salt (to taste)
Queso fresco (to taste)

Instructions:
Add everything to a 5 quart pot and once everything reaches a boil cook on medium heat for 90 minutes or until beans are tender.

In a separate cast iron skillet fry bacon until it's fried half way, then add weenies and fry until slightly browned. Now add chorizo and cook until they're fried. At this point add onions and cook until translucent. Finally, add your tomatoes, garlic, serranos and cook everything together for an additional 7 kinites on medium heat! Add everything to your pot of beans + chicharron and cilantro. Cook everything on medium high heat and once it reaches a boil cook and cover on medium low heat for 15-20 minutes. If you feel like your beans need salt at this point, add salt to taste!

Birria Recipe:

For this entire meal we estimated (45.5 carbs) and so far it seems like I calculated right! I had birria, 1/2 cup frijoles charros + 1/2 cup mac salad!🙌🏻

Meat:
5 lbs chuck roast or espaldilla de res
1/2 onion
4 garlic cloves
2 bayleaves
6 guajillo peppers
2 pasilla ancho peppers
2 chiles de arbol

1 roasted tomato
1/4 tsp cumin
1 tsp peppercorns
2 whole cloves
1/2 stick cinnamon
3 tbsps chicken bouillon
Salt to taste
2 cups water you cooked chiles in

Instructions:
Cover your meat with water, add onion garlic and bayleaves. Once meat reaches a boil; clean your broth and add your dried chiles to your pot. 
Now blend together your softened peppers, onion, garlic cloves and bay leaves that you previously boiled, roasted tomato, spices, 3 tbsps chicken bouillon + salt to taste with 2 cups of water you cooked chiles in. Strain the sauce you blended and add it to your pot after that first boil and then cover on medium high heat for 2 hours or until your meat is fork tender.

Add some shredded birria meat + consome to your plate and top with cilantro, onion and spicy salsa if you'd like, then serve with my delicious Mexican Mac Salad and Frijoles Charros🔥
